It was a black Saturday in the city of Port Harcourt, Rivers State as over 31 persons were feared dead in an early morning stampede at an event organised by one of the new generation churches in the state. Eye witness account had it that the church located at Ada George part of Port Harcourt invited members of the public to come for its fourth edition of gifts and food items distribution to mark its anniversary, but some of the invitees arrived on Friday while others arrived as early as 6.30 am this morning for an event that was supposed to start by 9 am. The eyewitness added that said persons who were supposed to have a sports session arrived at about 8 am and opened the small gate which gave the surging crowd an opportunity to push in and got stampeded. No fewer than 21 persons were feared dead. -Advertisement- “The incident happened this morning. The church invited people for its fourth edition of food and gift items distribution. Some came on Friday while many others came as early as 6.30 am on Saturday. “Those who were engaged in sporting activities opened the small gate and the surging crowd wanted to gain access through the small gate and got stampeded. I counted about 31 dead bodies on the ground,” he said. He said many of the victims have been taken to a hospital in Port Harcourt. Other witnesses said thousands of people gathered at the venue as early as 2.000am and were trying to force their way into the premises resulting in a stampede and deaths. “A nursing mother with her newborn baby of about four months were victims. I had to leave the event when I saw the increasing number of people rushing to get things free. POLL “There was no crowd control. Ambulances, policemen and other security agencies have been rushing the injured and evacuating the dead bodies at the scene,” a nursing mother said.